            "image_lastmod": 1653004870,
            "region": "Asia",
            "population": "5607283",
            "descriptionFromReview": "Not gonna lie, I was pretty curious and kinda hyped before I came to Singapore. However, within 24 hours all of my curiosity turned into disappointment. Yes, Singapore is clean by any standards but especially by Asian standards. And yes, you have shopping malls, fancy skyscrapers and free toilets everywhere.   But beside from that Singapore is boring and has no soul. It just seems like Singapore tries to copy interesting parts of other countries and their nature. Take Cloud Forest for example which is nothing more than a copycat of an actual cloud forest. Floral Fantasy is trying to bring blossoms in the cold reality of concrete and glass of Singapore. Gardens by the Bay is a park which is hyped because of its supertrees but actually quite boring, if you go for a walk. Those plus several different examples create the impression that Singapore is like the one kid in class which is trying really hard to get the attention but still doesn't have any friends.   Also, Singapore is all about money. It's about seeing and being seen. It feels like a big show off, almost no matter where you go. Everything seems so superficial.  Prices are ridiculous, too. Because Singapore has a bare minimum of agriculture everything needs to get imported, which will hurt your bank balance... a lot.   Pros:  - you can hop from one air-con-zone to the next - clean, like to an extend where you'd eat from the street. This is impressive, not gonna lie.  - shopping heaven if you're into that and have the money to spend - Little India is great and offers tasty food for cheap prices if you don't mind hanging with the \"poor\" people - great airport with an incredible amount of connections in Asia and Oceania  Cons:  - expensive to an extend which seems unfathomable in Asia - pretentious AF - polished and hollow - actually boring  If you have some money to spend and love Gin, go to ATLAS. It offers over 1300 different Gins from around the world. Their creme brulee is great, too! ",
